│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ 1. Perform the optimization                                                                                                                                                               │
│ 2. Set the fast-math flags of the result to be compatible with both the outer and inner calls                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ For value flags, the result should have a flag set only if both the outer and inner have it set.                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ For rewrite flags, the result can have the union.                                                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ But the original bug is about introducing poison, which happens when the result has stricter flags than warranted.                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ So if we set the result's value flags to the intersection, then:                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ - Outer has `nnan`, inner has `!nnan` → result has `!nnan`                                                                                                                                │
│ - This means `copysign(x, z)` with `!nnan` won't be poison when z is NaN                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ This would fix the bug.                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ Let me try this approach.                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ In the optimization, instead of just replacing the operand, I should also adjust the fast-math flags.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ Looking at the ldexp example again, they do:                                                                                                                                              │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ II->setFastMathFlags(InnerFlags); // Or the inner flags.                                                                                                                                  │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ But that might be too conservative.                                                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ The proper way would be to intersect the value flags and union the rewrite flags.                                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ From FMF.h, there are helper functions:                                                                                                                                                   │
│ - `intersectRewrite()` for rewrite flags                                                                                                                                                  │
│ - `unionValue()` for value flags                                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ But I need the opposite: for value flags,                                                                                                                                                 │
